Lay the @British turkey steaks{2} on a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Spread the @garlic mayonnaise{1} thinly over each steak. Sprinkle on the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} to coat the steaks evenly. Drizzle with a little @oil{}. Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until the crumbs are golden and the turkey is cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}.

> The turkey is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pick the @rosemary{1/2%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Chop the @medium tomato{2} into roughly 1cm chunks.

Pop the @broccoli florets{200%g} onto another baking tray and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and rinse the @borlotti beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the onion. Stir and cook until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the rosemary and garlic and cook for ~{2%minutes} more, stirring frequently. Stir in the @red wine stock paste{4%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Dissolve the stock pot and reduce the heat to a simmer. Add the beans and cook until the sauce has thickened and the beans are piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and stir in the tomato. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Share the bean and tomato mixture between your #bowls{} and pop the broccoli alongside. Serve the crunchy turkey steak on top. ENJOY!